{
  "texts": [
    "Definition 3 (RND).",
    "The node 𝑋 𝑗 is added to 𝑅 𝑞 if and only if the following condition holds: ∀𝑋 𝑖 ∈ 𝑅 𝑞, dist 𝑋 𝑞, 𝑋 𝑗 < dist 𝑋 𝑖, 𝑋 𝑗 (Eq. 2) Definition 4 (RRND).",
    "For a relaxation factor 𝛼 ≥ 1, the node 𝑋 𝑗 is added to 𝑅 𝑞 if and only if the following condition holds:∀𝑋 𝑖 ∈ 𝑅 𝑞, dist 𝑋 𝑞, 𝑋 𝑗 < 𝛼 • dist 𝑋 𝑖, 𝑋 𝑗 (Eq. 3)Definition 5 (MOND).",
    "For an angle 𝜃 ≥ 60 •, the node 𝑋 𝑗 is added to 𝑅 𝑞 if and only if the following condition holds:∀𝑋 𝑖 ∈ 𝑅 𝑞, ∠ 𝑋 𝑗 𝑋 𝑞 𝑋 𝑖 > 𝜃 (Eq. 4)Figure 2 shows the results after applying different ND approaches on the candidate neighborhood list 𝐶 𝑞 = {𝑋 1, 𝑋 2, 𝑋 3, 𝑋 4 } for node 𝑋 𝑞. RND (Figure 2a) was first used in the context of vector search by HNSW [97].",
    "Other methods adopted RND including NSG [54], SPTAG [29] and ELPIS [11]."
  ]
}